      <hedline>
        <hl1>Amateur in the Best Sense</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Henry Aronson letter about Mar 25 article on computerized music in Broadway musicals says student quality productions should be applauded (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I wonder if the school cast of ''Annie Get Your Gun'' at St. Andrew's was more skilled than the ''squawky pubescent clarinetists'' of the band. More likely they were squawky pubescent singers, and that is much to the good. On the way to becoming a Broadway music director and conductor, I learned to love musicals while working on school productions. When did the standard for school shows become CD-quality performances? Show a DVD and avoid the subpar student talent altogether.</p>
        <p>Henry Aronson  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
